s in bread lines in London, infanticide, and even cannibalism throughout Europe.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705192,"age":35,"year":"1328","julianDay":2206102,"title":"First War of Scottish Independence","description":"The First War of Scottish Independence began after England invaded Scotland in 1296. The Treaty of Edinburgh was signed in 1328 which declared peace between the two kingdoms and brought the war to an end.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705193,"age":44,"year":"1337","toYear":"1453","julianDay":2209390,"title":"The Hundred Years' War","description":"The Hundred Years' War between France and England was largely due to the question of legitimate succession to the French crown.","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"When Idonea Lisle was born in 1293, in Chaffcombe, Somerset, England, her father, William de Lisle, was 34 and her mother, Agnes, was 23. She married Hugh de Beauchamp about 1314, in Somerset, England. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 1 daughter. She died about 1359, in Somerset, England, at the age of 67."},"et":{"1293–about 1359":"1293–umbes 1359","1293–1359":"1293–1359","1290–1337":"1290–1337","1325–1396":"1325–1396","1330–Female":"1330–Surnud","1260–1294":"1260–1294","1270–Female":"1270–Surnud","1330":"1330","1396":"1396","1294":"1294","1293":"1293","1260":"1260","1270":"1270","1290":"1290","1337":"1337","1315":"1315","1359":"1359","1325":"1325","about 1314":"umbes 1314","about 1325":"umbes 1325","1453":"1453","about 1359":"umbes 1359","about 1330":"umbes 1330","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","Somerset, England":"Somerset, England","Europe":"Europe","Lillesdon, Somerset, England":"Lillesdon, Somerset, England","Chaffcombe, Somerset, England":"Chaffcombe, Somerset, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1293–about 1359":"1293–noin 1359","1293–1359":"1293–1359","1290–1337":"1290–1337","1325–1396":"1325–1396","1330–Female":"1330–Kuollut","1260–1294":"1260–1294","1270–Female":"1270–Kuollut","1330":"1330","1396":"1396","1294":"1294","1293